@remark "Created with golded 7.23 (11.11.4)"

@node MAIN "ConfGui"

ConfGui is a program which creates graphical user interfaces for
configuration files. It uses the ReAction GUI system.
ConfGui makes your life easier if you have applications with a large
number of parameters. ConfGui doesn't start your application. It just
manipulates configuration files. Many applications have the option to
read the parametes from a file.

ConfGui can only be started from Shell. The template ist:
confgui G=GUI/K/A,C=CONFIG/K/A,S=SCREEN/K,CLOSE:
GUI: the file with the gui description
CONFIG: the configuration file which you want to manipulate
SCREEN: optional name of a pubscreen
CLOSE: save button changes to "save & close"

Example:
confgui g=s:indent.dlg c="work:.indent.pro"

ConfGui first reads the GUI file. Then it reads the configuration
file and overwrites the default values from the GUI file. (If the
configuration file doesn't exist a new file will be created).
When no error occured the GUI will be opened.

 @{"Gadget commands" link "Commands"}
